<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-16 px-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p class="mb-4">
      This Privacy Policy explains how personal data is collected, used, and protected when using this website.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">1. Responsible Entity</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The Repair Scanner by Aron Bienge<br />
      Rorschacherstrasse 46<br />
      9000 St. Gallen<br />
      Switzerland<br />
      Email:
<a href="mailto:contact@the-repair-scanner.com" class="underline">
contact@the-repair-scanner.com
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">2. General Information</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We take the protection of your personal data seriously. Personal data is processed in accordance with the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (revDSG) and, where applicable, the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">3. Data Collected Automatically</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">When you visit this website, the following data may be collected automatically:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
      <li>IP address (anonymized where possible)</li>
      <li>Date and time of access</li>
      <li>Browser type and version</li>
      <li>Operating system</li>
      <li>Referrer URL</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This data is used solely to ensure the technical operation, security, and optimization of the website.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">4. Contact Requests</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      If you contact us via email or contact forms, the information you provide (such as name and email address) will be used exclusively to process your request and will not be shared with third parties.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">5. Cookies</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This website may use technically necessary cookies. These cookies are required for the operation of the website and do not require explicit consent.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This website may be hosted using third-party infrastructure providers (e.g., Netlify). These providers may process technical data in order to deliver the website securely and reliably.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Personal data is stored only for as long as necessary to fulfill the intended purpose or to comply with legal obligations.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      You have the right to request information about your stored personal data, request correction, deletion, or restriction of processing, and object to the processing of your data, subject to applicable legal requirements.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">9. Changes</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time to reflect legal or technical changes.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm opacity-80 mt-8">Last updated: January 2026</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
